author: Andrew Greif
description: Journalism ran down Gosger at the post, needing all of the course's 1 3/16th miles to author a stunning comeback victory of the 150th Preakness at Baltimore’s Pimlico Race Course.
title: In comeback, Journalism wins 150th Preakness Stakes

author: Andrew Jones
description: Austria was crowned the winner at Saturday’s grand finale of the Eurovision Song Contest, the world’s most popular singing tournament, beating strong competition from Israel and Switzerland to come in first place on an evening full of glitz and glamour.
title: Austria wins Eurovision with JJ's operatic club jam 'Wasted Love'

author: The Associated Press
description: The Caitlin Clark-Angel Reese rivalry added another chapter Saturday when Reese took exception to Clark’s hard foul in the third quarter as the Indiana Fever and Chicago Sky opened their seasons.
title: Caitlin Clark says flagrant foul for shoving Angel Reese was not ‘malicious’

author: Dennis Romero
description: At least 25 people have perished in severe weather that swept across Missouri and Kentucky over the weekend, authorities said.
title: At least 25 dead as tornadoes and thunderstorms devastate parts of Kentucky, Missouri

author: Yamiche Alcindor
description: Decades-old artifacts related to slavery and civil rights are rotating out of exhibits at the African American History Museum, as a potential White House review looms.
title: Critics question why exhibits at the African American History Museum are rotating out

author: Viola Flowers
description: Wells Enterprises, the company that produces Blue Bunny and Halo Top ice cream, has recalled nearly 18,000 containers of ice cream and frozen yogurt due to batches possibly containing pieces of plastic.
title: Nearly 18,000 containers of ice cream recalled for potential plastic contamination

description: At least 18 people have died in Kentucky following severe weather that swept through Missouri and Kentucky. Gov. Andy Beshear said the fatalities were caused by a single tornado, initially estimated to be an EF3.
title: At least 18 dead after powerful tornado ripped through Kentucky

description: Three of ten inmates who escaped from a New Orleans jail were apprehended, while authorities continue to search for seven others in the jailbreak that may have had inside help, officials said. Three employees have been placed on leave without pay and an investigation is underway
title: 3 of 10 inmates recaptured after escape from New Orleans jail

description: At least one person is dead after a car exploded in Palm Springs, California, a law enforcement source familiar with the investigation said. The identity and involvement of the deceased person in the explosion is not yet clear.
title: Deadly car explosion under investigation in Palm Springs

author: Andrew Blankstein
description: LOS ANGELES — One person is dead after a car exploded in Palm Springs, California, a law enforcement source familiar with the investigation said.
title: At least one dead after car explosion in Palm Springs

author: The Associated Press
description: The new standards raised red flags even among state School Superintendent Ryan Walters’ fellow Republicans, including the governor and legislative leaders.
title: New standards for Oklahoma high school students promote misinformation about 2020 election

author: Matt Lavietes
description: Former New England Patriots football coach Bill Belichick is hoping to set the record straight on his working relationship with his 24-year-old girlfriend, Jordon Hudson.
title: Bill Belichick addresses 24-year-old girlfriend's 'job responsibilities' amid viral interview fallout

description: Tim Layden looks back at the storied history of the Preakness while looking forward to a new chapter with the upcoming demolition of Pimlico Race Course.
title: How the Preakness straddles the past and a new era

author: Viola Flowers
description: The day before Tiffany Slaton’s 28th birthday, she was looking forward to eating a pack of Dunkaroos — cookies with frosting dip — that she’d saved as a makeshift birthday cake.
title: Hiker missing for 3 weeks details her survival journey in California mountains

author: Viola Flowers
description: Jimmy Fallon and The Weeknd crashed a Fordham University graduation party in New York City on Thursday, surprising this year's graduates with performances of hit songs "Blinding Lights" and "Can't Feel My Face."
title: 'They have no idea': Jimmy Fallon and The Weeknd shock Fordham University grads with surprise performance

description: Video captured across Missouri and Kentucky showed the extensive damage left in the aftermath of severe storms and suspected tornadoes. The death toll across the two states continues to increase in the day after the storms.
title: Missouri and Kentucky storms leave buildings damaged and trees scattered

author: Viola Flowers
description: Pedro Pascal, one of the stars of Ari Aster’s new modern Western “Eddington,” spoke carefully at the Cannes Film Festival when asked about recent deportations in the U.S.
title: Pedro Pascal, the son of immigrants, delicately addresses U.S. deportations

author: Rich Schapiro
description: Abdul Rahman Waziri, an Afghan who risked his life to protect U.S. Green Berets, made it to America after the war, only to be killed in a dispute about parking
title: A war hero was killed in a Texas parking lot. Why was the gunman not arrested?

author: Leslie Josephs, CNBC
description: President Donald Trump blasted Walmart on Saturday after the retailer warned this week that it will raise prices because of tariffs.
title: Trump tells Walmart to 'eat the tariffs' after retailer warned it will raise prices

author: Alexandra Marquez
description: President Donald Trump on Saturday said that he'll speak separately to Russian President Vladimir Putin and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy on Monday as he ramps up efforts to help the two nations reach a ceasefire.
title: Trump says he'll speak separately to Putin and Zelenskyy about a potential ceasefire

author: The Associated Press
description: NEW YORK — Greeted by a rare standing jeer in his return to Yankee Stadium, Juan Soto stepped out of the batter’s box, took off his helmet, tipped it to the crowd and touched it against his heart.
title: Juan Soto greeted with standing jeer in Yankee Stadium return

author: Matt Lavietes
description: A gunman entered a Las Vegas Athletic Club on Friday and shot multiple people, killing one and injuring several others.
title: One killed, multiple injured in shooting at Las Vegas gym

author: The Associated Press
description: Iran’s president said his country will continue talks with the United States over its rapidly advancing nuclear program but will not withdraw from its rights because of U.S. threats.
title: Iran says it will continue nuclear talks with the U.S., shrugging off Trump’s threats

author: Tim Stelloh
description: A judge’s ruling to resentence Erik and Lyle Menendez last week gave the siblings something they’ve not had in more than three decades: a chance that they could leave the Southern California prison where they’re incarcerated.
title: The Menendez brothers got a major win in their fight for freedom. But it's not over yet.

description: Authorities are continuing to search for seven of the 10 inmates who escaped from a New Orleans jail on Friday. Three others were apprehended Friday night. Law enforcement officials urge the public to remain alert and share any information they may have. NBC’s Ryan Chandler reports for Saturday TODAY.
title: Search underway for inmates who escaped New Orleans jail

description: Severe weather, including possible tornadoes, hit Missouri and Kentucky Friday, leaving at least 16 people dead and dozens injured, according to authorities. NBC’s Shaquille Brewster reports and Saturday TODAY’s Angie Lassman tracks the storm’s projected path.
title: Tornadoes hit Missouri, Kentucky, leaving at least 16 dead

author: Erik Ortiz
description: On red carpets from Los Angeles to the French Riviera, Sean “Diddy” Combs and the R&B singer Cassie intertwined arms, radiating an attractive and carefree façade for the cameras.
title: Cassie's graphic testimony of 'freak offs' may set the stage for what's to come in Diddy's trial

author: Aarne Heikkila
description: A human smuggler tells a potential customer in an audio message in Mandarin that there are now two potential sea routes for illegally entering the U.S.
title: Ocean patrols and narcotics playbooks: How a Florida city is tackling human smuggling

author: The Associated Press
description: Sovereignty is not running out of that starting gate in the Preakness Stakes on Saturday, two weeks after winning the Kentucky Derby.
title: Another Kentucky Derby winner not in the Preakness reignites debate about Triple Crown changes

author: Shiv Sudhakar, M.D.
description: Many Americans are really stressed out right now.  But we’re probably wrong about how stress affects our eating habits, new research suggests.
title: Stress eating doesn't always mean craving more: What to know to avoid overeating

author: Jeremy Mikula
description: A retail giant is raising prices, the White House is welcoming refugees, and Cassie Ventura takes the stand. Test your knowledge of the week in news.
title: A streaming service re-rebrands and an infamous baseball ban is lifted: The news quiz

author: Natasha Korecki
description: In autism circles and beyond, Temple Grandin’s story is well known.
title: As autism ignites a national conversation, Temple Grandin has something to say

author: The Associated Press
description: A Russian drone struck a passenger bus in Ukraine’s northeastern Sumy region on Saturday, killing nine people and injuring four others, Ukrainian officials said.
title: A Russian drone strike in northeastern Ukraine kills 9 people, officials say

author: Laura Strickler
description: Secret Service agents interviewed James Comey about his “8647” social media post. Administration officials called it a death threat against President Trump. Comey called it a political statement.
title: Secret Service agents question Comey about his Trump social media post

author: Phil Helsel
description: A dust storm that brought visibility to near zero swept across the Chicago area Friday, prompting the first dust storm warning ever issued to the city, officials said.
title: Dust storm covers Chicago with near-zero visibility conditions

author: Kalhan Rosenblatt
description: Republican lawmakers have introduced legislation that could give the federal government a tighter grasp on some tech platforms, while easing up scrutiny on AI.
title: Republicans seek to boost AI while tightening grip on social media and online speech

author: Katherine Doyle
description: Tensions between Trump and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu were already bubbling up before the president visited three of America’s key Arab allies.
title: Netanyahu is the odd man out in Trump’s Middle East trip

author: Ken Dilanian
description: Newly released audio of a special counsel interviewing then-President Biden confirms memory lapses that White House officials denied at the time.
title: Audio of interview confirms Biden memory lapses

author: Ken Dilanian
description: The Trump Administration has decided to permit the sale of devices that enable standard firearms to fire like machine guns, a move that gun control groups condemned.
title: Trump admin permits sale of device that allows standard firearms to fire like machine guns

description: Authorities say nine inmates are still on the run after ten inmates who authorities considered “armed and dangerous” escaped a New Orleans jail overnight. So far only one has been recaptured. NBC News’ Priya Sridhar reports.
title: Urgent search for Louisiana escaped inmates
